{"url": "https://www.ics.uci.edu/~aburtsev/143A/2017fall/index.html", "content": "<HTML>\n<HEAD>\n<META http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=US-ASCII\">\n<TITLE>143A Principles of Operating Systems</TITLE>\n<LINK HREF=\"./css/main.css\" TYPE=\"text/css\" REL=\"stylesheet\">\n<META NAME=\"Description\" CONTENT=\"Home page of Anton Burtsev.\">\n<META NAME=\"Keywords\" CONTENT=\"Anton Burtsev, Burtsev, Anton, cs5460\">\n<SCRIPT SRC=\"./scripts/image_switcher.js\" LANGUAGE=\"JavaScript\"></SCRIPT>\n</HEAD>\n\n<BODY BGCOLOR=\"#FFFFFF\" LEFTMARGIN=\"0\" TOPMARGIN=\"0\" MARGINWIDTH=\"0\" MARGINHEIGHT=\"0\">\n\t<TABLE  ID=\"text\" ALIGN=\"CENTER\" WIDTH=\"600\" BORDER=\"0\" CELLPADDING=\"0\" CELLSPACING=\"0\">\n\t<TR>\n\t\t<TD ALIGN=\"LEFT\" BGCOLOR=\"#FFFFFF\"><!-- top margin --> \n\t\t\t<IMG SRC=\"./images/spacer.gif\" WIDTH=\"100%\" HEIGHT=\"15\" ALT=\"\" BORDER=\"0\"/>\n\t\t</TD>\n\t</TR>\n\t<TR>\n\t<TD>\n\t\t<DIV ID=\"tech_nav\">\n\t\t\t<A HREF=\"../index.html\">Home</A>\n\t\t\t<IMG SRC=\"./images/spacer.gif\" WIDTH=\"100%\" HEIGHT=\"30\" ALT=\"\" BORDER=\"0\"/>\n\t\t</DIV>\n\t</TD>\n\t</TR>\t\n\t<TR>\n\t<TD COLSPAN=\"4\" ALIGN=\"LEFT\" BGCOLOR=\"#FFFFFF\">\n\n                <P ID=\"header\">143A</p>\n                <P id=\"header\">Principles of Operating Systems</P>\n\n<!--                <IMG SRC=\"./images/oswar.png\" WIDTH=\"250\" ALT=\"\"/> -->\n\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Fall 2017, University of California, Irvine</B></DIV>\n\t\t<DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Instructor: <A HREF=\"https://www.ics.uci.edu/~aburtsev\">Anton Burtsev</A></B></DIV> \n\n\t\t<DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Email: </B>aburtsev at uci at edu</DIV> \n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Office: </B><a href=\"https://eee.uci.edu/toolbox/roomfinder/room.php?building_abbr=DBH\">DBH 3066</a></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Meeting time/place:</B> Mon/Wed/Fri, 9:00-9:50am (<a href=\"https://eee.uci.edu/toolbox/roomfinder/room.php?building_abbr=SSLH\">SSLH 100</a>)</DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Anton's office ours: </B><b>Update:</b>Fri 4:30-5:30pm (<a href=\"https://eee.uci.edu/toolbox/roomfinder/room.php?building_abbr=DBH\">DBH 3066</a>)</DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>TAs' office ours: </B>Tue/Thu 4:30-5:30pm (<a href=\"https://eee.uci.edu/toolbox/roomfinder/room.php?building_abbr=ICS\">ICS CS424F</a>)</DIV>\n\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Discussion section: </B>Fri 12:00-12:50pm (<a href=\"https://eee.uci.edu/toolbox/roomfinder/room.php?building_abbr=EH\">EH 1200</a>)</DIV>\n\t\t<DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Mailing list (general announcements): </B><A HREF=\"ics143a-F17@classes.uci.edu\">ics143a-F17 at classes.uci.edu</a></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Piazza (discussion and questions): </B><a href=\"http://piazza.com/uci/fall2017/ics143a/home\">piazza.com/uci/fall2017/ics143a/home</a></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Other links:</b> <a href=\"https://canvas.eee.uci.edu/courses/6422\">Canvas</a></div>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Grading policy: </B> Homework: 60%, midterm exam: 15%, final exam: 25% of your grade.</DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Late homework policy: </B> You can submit late homework 3 days after the deadline for 60% of your grade.</DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Previous years: </B> <A href=\"../2017winter\">143A Winter 2017</a>.</DIV>\n                <div id=\"menu_caption\"><b>Andromeda Vagrant xv6 setup</b> <a href=\"http://www.ics.uci.edu/~aburtsev/143A/hw/xv6-setup.html\">instructions</a>.</div>\n                <div id=\"menu_caption\"><b>Links to all documents used in this class</b>: <a href=\"doc/refs.html\">References</a>.</div>\n\n                </P>\n\n                <P>\n\t\t<DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Schedule</B></DIV>\n\t\t<P>\n\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Sep 29:</B></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture01-intro/lecture01-intro.pdf\">Lecture 01 - Introduction</A> (<a href=\"videos/lecture01-introduction.mp4\">Audio</a>).</div> \n                <div id=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"http://pages.cs.wisc.edu/~remzi/OSTEP/intro.pdf\">OSTEP: 2 Introduction</A>.</DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><b>Discussion: </b><A HREF=\"./discussions/discussion01-intro.pdf\">Discussion 01 - Accessing Andromeda and basic UNIX commands</A>.</DIV>\n\n\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Oct 02:</B></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture02-os-interface/lecture02-os-interface.pdf\">Lecture 02 - OS Interfaces</A> (<a href=\"videos/lecture02-os-interface.mp4\">Video</a>).</div>\n                <div id=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"https://pdos.csail.mit.edu/6.828/2016/xv6/book-rev9.pdf\">xv6: Chapter 0: Operating system interfaces</A>.</DIV>\n                <div id=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"http://pages.cs.wisc.edu/~remzi/OSTEP/cpu-api.pdf\">OSTEP: Chapter 5: Interlude: Process API</a></div>\n\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Oct 04:</B>(cancelled)</DIV>\n                <div id=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"https://eprint.iacr.org/2016/086.pdf\">Intel SGX Explained: Section 2: Computer Architecture Background</A>.</div>\n                <div  ID=\"menu_item\"><B><A href=\"./hw/hw1-shell.html\">HW1: Shell</a> (due Fri October 13, 11:59pm Pacific Time)</B></DIV>\n\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Oct 06:</B></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture03-pc-hardware/lecture03-pc-hardware.pdf\">Lecture 03 (part 1) - PC Hardware</A>, <A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture03-pc-hardware/lecture03-memory-hierarchy.pdf\">Lecture 03 (part 2) - Memory Hierarchy</A> (<a href=\"videos/lecture03-pc-hardware.mp4\">Video</a>).</div>\n                <div id=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"https://eprint.iacr.org/2016/086.pdf\">Intel SGX Explained: Section 2: Computer Architecture Background</A>.</div>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><b>Discussion: </b><A HREF=\"./discussions/discussion02-booting-xv6.pdf\">Discussion 02 - Setting up and booting xv6 in Vagrant</A> (<a href=\"videos/discussion02-booting-xv6.mp4\">Video</a>).</DIV>\n\n\n\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Oct 9:</B></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture04-calling-conventions/lecture04-calling-conventions.pdf\">Lecture 04 - Calling conventions</A> (<a href=\"videos/lecture04-calling-conventions.mp4\">Video</a>).</div>\n                <div id=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"https://pdos.csail.mit.edu/6.828/2014/readings/pcasm-book.pdf\">PC Assembly Language. Paul A. Carter: Section 4 Subprograms (4.1 - 4.5)</A>, \n                and <A HREF=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/X86_calling_conventions\">Wikipedia: x86 calling conventions</A></div>\n\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Oct 11:</B></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture05-address-translation/lecture05-address-translation.pdf\">Lecture 05 - Address translation</A> (<a href=\"videos/lecture05-address-translation.mp4\">Video</a>).</div>\n                <div ID=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"https://software.intel.com/sites/default/files/managed/7c/f1/253668-sdm-vol-3a.pdf\">Intel\u00ae 64 and IA-32 architectures software developer's manual volume 3A: System programming guide, part 1 (Chapter 3: 3.1-3.4.5 and Chapter 4: 4.2-4.3)</A></div>\n\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Oct 13:</B></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture06-address-translation-part2/lecture06-address-translation-part2.pdf\">Lecture 06 - Address translation (Part 2: Paging)</A> (<a href=\"videos/lecture06-address-translation-part2.mp4\">Video</a>).</div>\n                <div ID=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"https://software.intel.com/sites/default/files/managed/7c/f1/253668-sdm-vol-3a.pdf\">Intel\u00ae 64 and IA-32 architectures software developer's manual volume 3A: System programming guide, part 1 (Chapter 3: 3.1-3.4.5 and Chapter 4: 4.2-4.3)</A></div>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><b>Discussion: </b><A HREF=\"./discussions/discussion03-c-primer.pdf\">Discussion 03 - C Primer</A> (<a href=\"videos/discussion03-c-primer.mp4\">Video</a>).</DIV>\n\n\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Oct 16:</B></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture07-system-boot/lecture07-system-boot.pdf\">Lecture 07 - System boot</A> (<a href=\"videos/lecture07-system-boot.mp4\">Video</a>).\n                <B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"https://pdos.csail.mit.edu/6.828/2016/xv6/book-rev9.pdf\">Appendix B: The boot loader and Chapter 1: Code: the first address space</A></div>\n                <div  ID=\"menu_item\"><B><A href=\"./hw/hw2-boot-xv6.html\">HW2: Boot xv6</a> (UPDATE: due Wed October 25, 11:59pm Pacific Time)</B></DIV>\n\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Oct 18:</B></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture08-process-arch/lecture08-process-arch.pdf\">Lecture 08 - Basic architecture of a process</A> (<a href=\"videos/lecture08-process-arch.mp4\">Video</a>).</div>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><B>Source code examples:</B> <A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture08-process-arch/src/\">Source</A></div>\n\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"http://pages.cs.wisc.edu/~remzi/OSTEP/vm-intro.pdf\">OSTEP: Chapter 13: The Abstraction: Address Spaces</A></div>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"http://pages.cs.wisc.edu/~remzi/OSTEP/vm-api.pdf\">OSTEP: Chapter 14: Interlude: Memory API</A></div>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"http://pages.cs.wisc.edu/~remzi/OSTEP/vm-mechanism.pdf\">OSTEP: Chapter 15.1-15.3: Mechanism: Address Translation</A></div>\n\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Oct 20:</B></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture08-process-arch/lecture08-process-arch-part2.pdf\">Lecture 09 - Basic architecture of a process (part 2)</A> (<a href=\"videos/lecture08-process-arch-part2.mp4\">Video</a>).</div>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><B>Source code examples:</B> <A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture08-process-arch/src/\">Source</A> (look for the readme.txt for how to compile and use the tools, e.g., objdump, readelf)</div>\n\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"https://github.com/tuhdo/os01/files/828054/Operating_System_From_0_to_1.pdf\">OS 0 to 1: Chapter 4: x86 assembly and C</A>.</div>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"https://github.com/tuhdo/os01/files/828054/Operating_System_From_0_to_1.pdf\">OS 0 to 1: Chapter 5: The Anatomy of a Program</A>.</div>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><B>Optional Reading:</B> (that will help with homework if you have never seen GDB) <A HREF=\"https://github.com/tuhdo/os01/files/828054/Operating_System_From_0_to_1.pdf\">OS 0 to 1: Chapter 6: Runtime inspection and debugging</A>.</div>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><b>Discussion: </b><A HREF=\"./discussions/discussion04-gdb.pdf\">Discussion 04 - GDB</A> (<a href=\"videos/discussion04-gdb.mp4\">Video</a>).</DIV>\n\n\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Oct 23:</B></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture09-kernel-init/lecture09-kernel-init.pdf\">Lecture 09 - System Init</A> (<a href=\"videos/lecture09-system-init.mp4\">Video</a>).</div>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"https://pdos.csail.mit.edu/6.828/2016/xv6/book-rev9.pdf\">Chapter 2: Page tables (up to \"User part of an address space\")</A>.</div>\n\n\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Oct 27:</B></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture10-address-spaces/lecture10-address-spaces.pdf\">Lecture 10 - Address Spaces (Kernel memory allocator)</A> (<a href=\"videos/lecture10-address-spaces.mp4\">Video</a>).\n                <B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"https://pdos.csail.mit.edu/6.828/2016/xv6/book-rev9.pdf\">Chapter 2: Page tables (up to \"User part of an address space\").</A></div>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><b>Discussion: </b><A HREF=\"./discussions/discussion05-paging.pdf\">Discussion 05 - Paging</A> (<a href=\"videos/discussion05-paging.mp3\">Audio</a>).</DIV>\n\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Oct 30:</B></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture10-address-spaces/lecture10-address-spaces-part2.pdf\">Lecture 10 - Address Spaces (4K page table)</A> (<a href=\"videos/lecture10-address-spaces-part2.mp4\">Video</a>).</div>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"https://pdos.csail.mit.edu/6.828/2016/xv6/book-rev9.pdf\">Chapter 2: Page tables (up to \"User part of an address space\").</A></div>\n                <div  ID=\"menu_item\"><B><A href=\"./hw/hw3-hello.html\">HW3: Hello world</a> (due Mon Nov 6, 11:59pm Pacific Time)</B></DIV>\n\n\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Nov 1:</B></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture11-creating-processes/lecture11-creating-processes.pdf\">Lecture 11 - Creating processes</A> (<a href=\"videos/lecture11-creating-processes.mp4\">Video</a>).</div>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"https://pdos.csail.mit.edu/6.828/2016/xv6/book-rev9.pdf\">Chapter 2: Page tables.</A></div>\n\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Nov 3:</B></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture12-interrupts/lecture12-interrupts.pdf\">Lecture 12 - Interrupts</A> (<a href=\"videos/lecture12-interrupts.mp4\">Video</a>).</div>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"https://pdos.csail.mit.edu/6.828/2016/xv6/book-rev9.pdf\">Chapter 3: Traps, interrupts and drivers.</A></div>\n\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Nov 6:</B></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture12-interrupts/lecture12-interrupts-part2.pdf\">Lecture 12 - Interrupts (part 2)</A> (<a href=\"videos/lecture12-interrupts-part2.mp4\">Video</a>).</div>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"https://pdos.csail.mit.edu/6.828/2016/xv6/book-rev9.pdf\">Chapter 3: Traps, interrupts and drivers.</A></div>\n\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Nov 8:</B></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture13-context-switch/lecture13-context-switch.pdf\">Lecture 13 - Context switch</A> (<a href=\"videos/lecture13-context-switch.mp4\">Video</a>).</div>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"https://pdos.csail.mit.edu/6.828/2016/xv6/book-rev9.pdf\">Chapter 1. Subsection: Running the first process, Chapter 5 - Scheduling (up until Sllep and Wakeup).</A></div>\n\n\n<!--\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Oct 25:</B></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture12-other-cpus/lecture12-other-cpus.pdf\">Lecture 12 - Starting other CPUs</A>.\n                </div>\n-->\n\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Nov 13:</B></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture14-syscalls/lecture14-syscalls.pdf\">Lecture 14 - System calls and the first process</A> (<a href=\"videos/lecture14-syscalls.mp4\">Video</a>).</div>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"https://pdos.csail.mit.edu/6.828/2016/xv6/book-rev9.pdf\">Chapter 1. Subsection: Code: creating the first process, Chapter 3 - The first system call (up until Drivers).</A></div>\n\n\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Nov 15:</B></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture-midterm-recap/lecture-midterm-recap.pdf\">Lecture  - Midterm recap</A> (<a href=\"videos/midterm-recap.mp4\">Video</a>).</div>.\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"https://pdos.csail.mit.edu/6.828/2016/quiz.html\">Example midterms from MIT</a> (note, MIT is more advanced class, so don't get scared).</div>\n\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Nov 17:</B></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><A HREF=\"./midterm/paper.pdf\">Midterm exam</a></div>\n                \n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Nov 20:</B></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture14-syscalls/lecture14-syscalls-part2.pdf\">Lecture 14 - System calls (part 2)</A> (<a href=\"videos/lecture14-syscalls-part2.mp4\">Video</a>).</div>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"https://pdos.csail.mit.edu/6.828/2016/xv6/book-rev9.pdf\">Chapter 1. Subsection: Code: creating the first process, Chapter 3 - The first system call (up until Drivers).</A></div>\n\n\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Nov 22:</B></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture15-locking/lecture15-locking.pdf\">Lecture 15 - Locking</A> (<a href=\"videos/lecture15-locking.mp4\">Video</a>).</div>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"https://pdos.csail.mit.edu/6.828/2016/xv6/book-rev9.pdf\">xv6: Chapter 4: Locking</a></div>\n                <div  ID=\"menu_item\"><B><A href=\"./hw/hw4-syscalls.html\">HW4: Syscalls</a> (due Fri Dec 1, 11:59pm Pacific Time)</B></DIV>\n\n\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Nov 27:</B></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture16-locking-part2/lecture16-locking-part2.pdf\">Lecture 15 - Locking (continued)</A> (<a href=\"videos/lecture15-locking-part2.mp4\">Video</a>).</div>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"https://pdos.csail.mit.edu/6.828/2016/xv6/book-rev9.pdf\">xv6: Chapter 5: Scheduling</a></div>\n\n\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Nov 29:</B></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture16-file-system/lecture16-file-system.pdf\">Lecture 16 - File System (Intro, Buffer Cache)</A> (<a href=\"videos/lecture16-file-system.mp4\">Video</a>).</div>\n                <div id=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"https://pdos.csail.mit.edu/6.828/2016/xv6/book-rev9.pdf\">xv6: Chapter 6: File System</a></div>\n                <div id=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"http://pages.cs.wisc.edu/~remzi/OSTEP/file-implementation.pdf\">OSTEP: Chapter 40: File System Implementation</a></div>\n\n\t\t<DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Dec 1:</B></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture17-memory-management/lecture17-memory-management-tex.pdf\">Lecture 17 - Memory Management</A> (<a href=\"videos/lecture17-memory-management.mp4\">Video</a>).</div>\n                <div id=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"https://www.kernel.org/doc/gorman/html/understand/understand009.html\">Mel Gorman. \"Understanding the Linux Virtual Memory Manager\", Chapter 6 Physical Page Allocation</a></div>\n                <div id=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"https://www.kernel.org/doc/gorman/html/understand/understand011.html\">Mel Gorman. \"Understanding the Linux Virtual Memory Manager\", Chapter 8 Slab Allocator</a></div>\n                <div id=\"menu_item\"><b>Discussion:</b> <a href=\"http://replay.uci.edu/uci-only/fall2017/Dec_1_disc_edited_-_20171205_001255_11.html\">Midterm solutions</a></div>\n                <div  ID=\"menu_item\"><B><A href=\"./hw/hw5-infinite-files.html\">HW5: Infinite Files</a> (due Sunday, Dec 10, 11:59pm, Pacific Time)</B></DIV>\n\n        \n<!--\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Feb 27:</B></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture18-file-system/lecture18-file-system.pdf\">Lecture 18 - File System (Buffer Cache)</A>.</div>\n                <div id=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"https://pdos.csail.mit.edu/6.828/2016/xv6/book-rev9.pdf\">xv6: Chapter 6: File System</a></div>\n\t\t<div id=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"http://pages.cs.wisc.edu/~remzi/OSTEP/file-implementation.pdf\">OSTEP: Chapter 40: File System Implementation</a></div>\n-->\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Dec 04:</B></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture16-file-system/lecture16-file-system.pdf\">Lecture 16 - File System (Logging)</A> (<a href=\"videos/lecture16-file-system-logging.mp4\">Video</a>).</div>\n                <div id=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"https://pdos.csail.mit.edu/6.828/2016/xv6/book-rev9.pdf\">xv6: Chapter 6: File System</a></div>\n\t\t<div id=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"http://pages.cs.wisc.edu/~remzi/OSTEP/file-implementation.pdf\">OSTEP: Chapter 40: File System Implementation</a></div>\n                <div ID=\"menu_item\"><B><A href=\"./hw/extra.html\">Extra credit assignments</a> (due Tue Dec 12, 4:59pm Pacific Time)</B></DIV>\n\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Dec 06:</B></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture16-file-system/lecture16-file-system.pdf\">Lecture 16 - File System (Inodes)</A> (<a href=\"videos/lecture16-file-system-inodes.mp4\">Video</a>).</div>\n                <div id=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"https://pdos.csail.mit.edu/6.828/2016/xv6/book-rev9.pdf\">xv6: Chapter 6: File System</a></div>\n\t\t<div id=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"http://pages.cs.wisc.edu/~remzi/OSTEP/file-implementation.pdf\">OSTEP: Chapter 40: File System Implementation</a></div>\n\n\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Dec 08:</B></DIV>\n\t\t<DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture18-scheduling/lecture18-scheduling.pdf\">Lecture 19 - Scheduling </A> (<a href=\"http://replay.uci.edu/media/public/fall2017/ics143-directory_-_20171208_100242_11.html\">Video</a>).</div>\n\n\t\t<div id=\"menu_item\"> <B>Reading:</B><a\nhref=\"https://www.amazon.com/Linux-Kernel-Development-Robert-Love/dp/0672329468\">Robert Love. Linux Kernel Development. Chapter 4: Process Scheduling (up until Fair\nScheduling)</a> (click \"Look inside\", page 46 is available through Google Books <a href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=3MWRMYRwulIC&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=false\">here</a>).</div>\n\n\t\t<div id=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B><A href=\"http://pages.cs.wisc.edu/~remzi/OSTEP/cpu-sched.pdf\">OSTEP: Chapter 7: CPU Scheduling</a></div> \n\n\t\t<div id=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B><A href=\"http://pages.cs.wisc.edu/~remzi/OSTEP/cpu-sched-mlfq.pdf\">OSTEP: Chapter 8: Multi-level Feedback</a></div>\n\t        <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><b>Discussion: </b><A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture-final-recap/lecture-final-recap.pdf\">Discussion - Final recap</A> (<a href=\"http://replay.uci.edu/media/public/fall2017/ics143a_-_final_recap_-_20171208_125826_11.html\">Video</a>).</DIV>\n\n\t        <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture-final-recap/sample-questions.html\"><b>Sample questions for the final </b></A>.</DIV>\n\n\n\n<!--                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>March 03:</B></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\">Discussion of the system call homework</div>\n\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>March 06:</B></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture18-file-system/lecture18-file-system.pdf\">Lecture 18 - File System (Inodes, file descriptors, files)</A>.</div>\n                <div id=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B> <A HREF=\"https://pdos.csail.mit.edu/6.828/2016/xv6/book-rev9.pdf\">xv6: Chapter 6: File System</a></div>\n                <div id=\"menu_item\"><B>Whiteboard picture:</B><A HREF=\"https://goo.gl/photos/wD9q7rHuxJT1CUXC6\">File system</a></div>\n                <div  ID=\"menu_item\"><B><A href=\"./hw/hw4-big-files.html\">HW4: Big files</a> (due March 17st, 11:59pm)</B></DIV>\n\n\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>March 10:</B></DIV>\n\t\t<DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture19-scheduling/lecture19-scheduling.pdf\">Lecture 19 - Scheduling (Completely Fair Scheduler)</A>.</div> \n\n\t\t<div id=\"menu_item\"><B>Reading:</B><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Linux-Kernel-Development-Robert-Love/dp/0672329468\">Robert Love. Linux Kernel Development. Chapter 4: Process Scheduling (up until The Linux Scheduling Implementation)</a> (click \"Look inside\", page 46 is available through Google Books <a\nhref=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=3MWRMYRwulIC&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=false\">here</a>).</div>\n\n\n      \n\n\t\t<DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>March 15:</B></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture21-linking-and-loading/lecture21-linking-and-loading.pdf\">Lecture 21 - Linking and Loading</A>.\n                <B>Reading:</B>Linkers and Loaders (John Levine)</div> \n\n\t\t<DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>March 17:</B></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><A HREF=\"./lectures/lecture-final-recap/lecture-final-recap.pdf\">Lecture 22 - Final Recap</A>.\n                <B>Whiteboard pictures:</b><a href=\"https://goo.gl/photos/PdUeJTR7QfcX2CZL7\">Bootloader</a>, <a href=\"https://goo.gl/photos/yc58fkg2LHpRf1bT7\">lifecycle of a process<a><a href=\"https://goo.gl/photos/8QokuX3suuiFzMwD8\">address spaces</a>.</div>\n-->\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Dec 13:</B></DIV>\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"><A HREF=\"./final/paper.pdf\">Final exam</a></div>\n\n\n\t\t</DIV></P>\n                </P>\n\n\t\t<P>\n\t\t<DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Class overview</B></DIV>\n\n<P>143A teaches the fundamentals of operating systems. You will study, in\ndetail, virtual memory, kernel and user mode, system calls, threads, context\nswitches, interrupts, interprocess communication, coordination of concurrent\nactivities, and the interface between software and hardware. Most importantly,\nyou will study the interactions between these concepts, and how to manage the\ncomplexity introduced by the interactions.</P>\n\n<P>To master the concepts, 143A is organized in as a series of lectures,\nand homeworks. The lectures (and the book readings) familiarize you with the\nmain concepts. The homrworks force you to understand the concepts at a deep\nlevel.</P>\n\n<P>The lectures are based on <A\nHREF=\"https://pdos.csail.mit.edu/6.828/2016/xv6.html\">xv6 (x86 version 6)</A>,\nwhich is a modern re-implementation of one of the early UNIX operating systems, \nspecifically Unix Version 6 which was developed in the 1970s, on the modern hardware. \nxv6 is only 9,000 lines of C code, but it can run real processes, and perform many \nfunctions of a traditional operating system, e.g., Windows, Linux, and Mac OS. \nDue to its small size, it is possible to read the source code and understand the entire \noperating system. Moreover, xv6 is accompanied by a <A\nHREF=\"https://pdos.csail.mit.edu/6.828/2016/xv6/book-rev9.pdf\">book</A>\ndescribing its architecture (and a <A\nHREF=\"https://pdos.csail.mit.edu/6.828/2016/xv6/xv6-rev9.pdf\">printout of its\nsource code</A>).  Homework assignments will help you to deepen the\nunderstanding of the principles and internal organization of a simple, but real\noperating system.</P>\n\n<P>You may wonder why we are studying an operating system that resembles Unix\nv6 instead of the latest and greatest version of Linux, Windows, or BSD Unix.\nxv6 is big enough to illustrate the basic design and implementation ideas in\noperating systems. On the other hand, xv6 is far smaller than any modern\nproduction operating systems, and correspondingly easier to understand. xv6 has\na structure similar to many modern operating systems; once you've explored xv6\nyou will find that much is familiar inside kernels such as Linux.</P>\n\n\n\t\t</DIV> </P>\n\n\t\t<P> <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Prerequisites</B></DIV>\n\n\t\t<P>Xv6 is implemented in C, so you're expected to be familiar\nwith the C programming language. </P>\n\n\t\t<P>Xv6 runs in the QEMU simulator and on bare-metal. You're\nexpected to be familiar with the basics of Linux environment.</P>\n\n\n\n\t\t</P> \n\n\n\t        <P>\n\t\t<DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Books</B></DIV>\n\n\t\tThe class is based on two books that are freely available from\nthe authors: <DIV ID=\"menu_item\"> <P><A\nHREF=\"http://pages.cs.wisc.edu/~remzi/OSTEP/\">Operating Systems: Three Easy\nPieces</A> (free, available online). Remzi H.  Arpaci-Dusseau and Andrea C.\nArpaci-Dusseau</P> </DIV>\n\n\t\t<DIV ID=\"menu_item\"> <P><A\nHREF=\"https://pdos.csail.mit.edu/6.828/2016/xv6/book-rev9.pdf\">Xv6 a Simple,\nUnix-like Teaching Operating System</A> (free, available online). Russ Cox,\nFrans Kaashoek, Rober Morris</P> </DIV>\n\n                <DIV ID=\"menu_caption\"><B>Additional resources</B></DIV>\n                <P><A HREF=\"http://www.intel.com/content/www/us/en/processors/architectures-software-developer-manuals.html\">Intel 64 and IA-32 Architectures Software Developer's Manual (Combined volumes)</A></P>\n\n                <P><a href=\"https://github.com/tuhdo/os01\">Operating Systems: From 0 to 1</a> (<a href=\"https://github.com/tuhdo/os01/files/828054/Operating_System_From_0_to_1.pdf\">PDF</a>).\n\n                <P><a href=\"https://pdos.csail.mit.edu/6.828/2016/readings/pcasm-book.pdf\">PC Assembly Language</a>, Paul A. Carter, November 2003. \n\n                <P><a href=\"doc/refs.html\">All documents used in this class</a>.\n\n\t\t</DIV>\n\t\t</P>\n\t</TD>\t\t\t\n\t</TR>\n\t<TR>\n\t\t<TD ALIGN=\"LEFT\" BGCOLOR=\"#FFFFFF\"><!-- top margin --> \n\t\t\t<IMG SRC=\"./images/spacer.gif\" WIDTH=\"100%\" HEIGHT=\"15\" ALT=\"\" BORDER=\"0\"/>\n\t\t</TD>\n\t</TR>\n\t<TR>\n\t<TD COLSPAN=\"4\">\n\t\t<DIV ID=\"tech\">Updated: September, 2017</DIV>\n\t</TD>\n\t</TR>\n\t</TABLE>\n</BO